            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Thine image in the waters of my breast."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "type": "verse",
      "number": "2"
    },
    {
      "lines": [
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "When sinks the soul, subdued by toil, to slumber,"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Its closing eye looks up to Thee in prayer;"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Sweet the repose, beneath Thy wings o’ershadowing,"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "But sweeter still to wake and find Thee there."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "type": "verse",
      "number": "3"
    },
    {
      "lines": [
        {
          "segments": [
